name: Keystone Necklace
description:

Early builders used this innovation to be able to flood ancient buildings with natural light.

It's an important symbol, alluding to great strength, integrity, innovation, and the search for light and knowledge.

Also available in Sterling Silver with silver chain.

The Celestial Bodies Ring was hand carved to represent the sun nestled next to the crescent moon, finished with an etched starburst design and then cast in brilliant sterling silver. 

Ring sizes 6.5,7,8 available

Materials: Sterling Silver

High polished finish

name: Isis Necklace
description:
Our Isis Necklace, named after the most revered Egyptian goddess -- patroness of magic and nature, ideal mother, friend of slaves, sinners and artists, and protector of the dead. 


Comprised of antiqued brass ribbon chain as well as various gemstones, this is a piece fit for Egypt's most revered woman.


Materials: Gold plated chain, antiqued ribbon chain, copper fringe, raw agate, pyrite, spotted jasper, and quartz. Measures at 24" long with a 2" extender chain. Handmade in Brooklyn.


Agate: Offers protection and physical and spiritual healing. Governed by the moon. Wear when making a crucial decision. 

Pyrite: Excellent shield of negative energy. Promotes self-confidence, wear when attempting to seek the truth. 

Quartz: For meditation, amplifier of other gemstones surrounding it. 

Jasper: Giver of courage, governed by Mercury and Venus. 


Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Diana Necklace
description:
The Diana necklace is a simple yet strong everyday necklace named for the Roman goddess of the hunt. Antiqued brass ribbon chain connects to one center Pyrite bullet shaped horns and finished with gold plated findings.

It hangs at approximately 22 inches and has an adjustable 2 inch extender chain.

Materials: Antiqued Brass, Pyrite


Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Artemis Necklace
description:
Named after the Greek goddess of the moon, The Artemis Necklace is comprised of antique brass ribbon chain and organic raw cut lavender Agate stone. 

This necklace hangs at approximately 24'' long and is adjustable with a 2'' extender chain.

Material: Antiqued Brass Chain, Gold Plated Chain, Blue Lace Agate 

Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Fortuna Necklace
description:
The Fortuna Necklace is comprised of delicate gold filled chain, stunning organic purple Agate Chalcedony, and faceted pyrite. 

This necklace drapes elegantly across the collarbone and measures at approximately 20' long.

Material: Gold filled chain, Agate Chalcedony, Pyrite

name: Loli Necklace
description:
Loli, the Romani term meaning feminine and red, is the perfect way to describe this alluring rose gold necklace! The Loli necklace moves with snake-like elegance and consists of both rose gold and gold chain. 

Approximately 20' long

Materials: Rose Gold Plated Chain and 12K Gold Fill Chain

Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Kham Hand Harness
description:
Kham, the Gypsy word meaning "the Sun", was the basis for our simple and feminine rosy gold hand harness. The Kham Hand Harness is comprised of gorgeous rose gold "fishbone" chain and delicate gold curb chain. 

Adjustable bracelet design featuring a 2' extender chain.

Materials: Rose Gold Plate and 14K Gold Plate Chain

Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Baxt Earrings
description:
Baxt, the Romani word meaning "luck, fortune, and fate", inspired these delicate gold earrings! The Baxt Earrings are comprised of rose gold plated "fishbone" chain and gold findings. 

Approximate 2' drop.

Materials: Gold Fill Earwires, Gold Plate Spikes, and Rose Gold Plated Chain

Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Dji Necklace
description:
The Dji Necklace comes from the gypsy word meaning "soul". This intricate bib necklace rests gracefully across the collarbone lending the wearer a regal and tribal inspired vibe. 

This necklace is approximately 24' long.

Material: Rose Gold Plate Chain, Man-made Turquoise. 

Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Darro Earrings
description:
The Darro Earrings were created with ancient tribal elements in mind and feature rose gold plate chain and ear wires along with cut turquoise.  

These earrings hang at approximately 2". 

Material: Rose Gold Plate Chain, Man-made Turquoise 

Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Cama Bracelet
description:
The Cama Bracelet, named after the Romani word for "love", is comprised of rhodium plated fishbone chain, gold plated curb chain, aluminum rope chain, and gold plated findings. It is 6" around, complete with a 2" extender chain. 

Materials: Gold plate, rhodium, aluminum 


Always handmade in Brooklyn

name: Heron Ring in Sterling Silver
description:

Always handmade in Brooklyn
